hire, England":"英国林可爾史爾維其肯比","Petsoe Manor, Buckinghamshire, England":"英国巴金哈姆爾左 曼諾","Bedfordshire, England":"英国貝德福爾","Wickham, Hampshire, England":"英国哈普爾威克姆","lifeSummary":"Sir William Chamberlain Knight是Robert Chamberlayne的儿子，于大约1238年出生在英国林可爾史爾維其肯比。他于大约1261年与Mrs Joan Chamberlain在英国林可爾史爾諾斯 雷斯頓结婚。他们至少是1个儿子的父母。他去世于1285年之前在英国巴金哈姆爾左 曼諾。"},"hr":{"about 1238–before 1285":"oko 1238.–prije 1285.","1230–1284":"1230–1284","1230–Male":"1230–preminuo","1238–1285":"1238–1285","1251–1313":"1251–1313","1264–1314":"1264.–1314","1200–1260":"1200–1260.","about 1261":"oko 1261.","1264":"1264.","1285":"1285","1230":"1230","1251":"1251","1284":"1284","1260":"1260.","1238":"1238","1259":"1259","1314":"1314","1313":"1313","1200":"1200","about 1238":"oko 1238.","before 1285":"prije 1285.","North Reston, Lincolnshire, England":"North Reston, Lincolnshire, England","Wickenby, Lincolnshire, England":"Wickenby, Lincolnshire, England","Petsoe Manor, Buckinghamshire, England":"Petsoe Manor, Buckinghamshire, England","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, England","Wickham, Hampshire, England":"Wickham, Hampshire, England"},"cs":{"about 1238–before 1285":"okolo 1238–před 1285","1230–1284":"1230–1284","1230–Male":"1230–Zesnulý","1238–1285":"1238–1285","1251–1313":"1251–1313","1264–1314":"1264–1314","1200–1260":"1200–1260","about 1261":"okolo 1261","1264":"1264","1285":"1285","1230":"1230","1251":"1251","1284":"1284","1260":"1260","1238":"1238","1259":"1259","1314":"1314","1313":"1313","1200":"1200","about 1238":"okolo 1238","before 1285":"před 1285","North Reston, Lincolnshire, England":"North Reston, Lincolnshire, Anglie","Wickenby, Lincolnshire, England":"Wickenby, Lincolnshire, Anglie","Petsoe Manor, Buckinghamshire, England":"Petsoe Manor, Buckinghamshire, Anglie","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, Anglie","Wickham, Hampshire, England":"Wickham, Hampshire, Anglie"},"da":{"about 1238–before 1285":"omkring 1238–før 1285","1230–1284":"1230–1284","1230–Male":"1230–Afdød","1238–1285":"1238–1285","1251–1313":"1251–1313","1264–1314":"1264–1314","1200–1260":"1200–1260","about 1261":"omkring 1261","1264":"1264","1285":"1285","1230":"1230","1251":"1251","1284":"1284","1260":"1260","1238":"1238","1259":"1259","1314":"1314","1313":"1313","1200":"1200","about 1238":"omkring 1238","before 1285":"før 1285","North Reston, Lincolnshire, England":"North Reston, Lincolnshire, England","Wickenby, Lincolnshire, England":"Wickenby, Lincolnshire, England","Petsoe Manor, Buckinghamshire, England":"Petsoe Manor, Buckinghamshire, England","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, England","Wickham, Hampshire, England":"Wickham, Hampshire, England"},"nl":{"about 1238–before 1285":"circa 1238–vóór 1285","1230–1284":"1230–1284","1230–Male":"1230–Overleden","1238–1285":"1238–1285","1251–1313":"1251–1313","1264–1314":"1264–1314","1200–1260":"1200–1260","about 1261":"circa 1261","1264":"1264","1285":"1285","1230":"1230","1251":"1251","1284":"1284","1260":"1260","1238":"1238","1259":"1259","1314":"1314","1313":"1313","1200":"1200","about 1238":"circa 1238","before 1285":"vóór 1285","North Reston, Lincolnshire, England":"North Reston, Lincolnshire, England","Wickenby, Lincolnshire, England":"Wickenby, Lincolnshire, England","Petsoe Manor, Buckinghamshire, England":"Petsoe Manor, Buckinghamshire, England","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, England","Wickham, Hampshire, England":"Wickham, Hampshire, England"},"en":{"about 1238–before 1285":"about 1238–before 1285","1230–1284":"1230–1284","1230–Male":"1230–Deceased","1238–1285":"1238–1285","1251–1313":"1251–1313","1264–1314":"1264–1314","1200–1260":"1200–1260","about 1261":"about 1261","1264":"1264","1285":"1285","1230":"1230","1251":"1251","1284":"1284","1260":"1260","1238":"1238","1259":"1259","1314":"1314","1313":"1313","1200":"1200","about 1238":"about 1238","before 1285":"before 1285","North Reston, Lincolnshire, England":"North Reston, Lincolnshire, England","Wickenby, Lincolnshire, England":"Wickenby, Lincolnshire, England","Petsoe Manor, Buckinghamshire, England":"Petsoe Manor, Buckinghamshire, England","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, England","Wickham, Hampshire, England":"Wickham, Hampshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Chamberlain","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: status name from Old French <i>chambrelain</i>, Norman French <i>cambrelanc</i>, <i>cambrelen(c)</i> ‘chamberlain’ (of ancient Germanic origin, from <i>kamer</i> ‘chamber, room’, Latin <i>camera</i> (see   Chambers  ) + the diminutive suffix <i>-(l)ing</i>). This was originally the name of an official in charge of the private chambers of his master, but is so widespread in late medieval England that it must sometimes have been used of people of more ordinary status, perhaps as a nickname for an officious or self-important person or for someone who played the role of chamberlain in a folk play, tableau, or ceremony. Compare   Chancellor   for a possible similar usage."],"variants":[{"name":"Chamberlin","meanings":["English: variant of   Chamberlain  .","French: occupational name for an official in charge of the private chambers of his master, from Old French <i>chamberlenc</i> ‘chamberlain’. See also   Chamberlain   and compare above."]},{"name":"Chambers","meanings":["English:","from Middle English <i>chaumbre</i> ‘room (in a house); reception room in a palace or official building’ (Old French <i>chambre</i>). It is identical in implied function with the   Chamberlain  , which denoted an official: to pay <i>in cameram</i> was to pay into the exchequer, of which the <i>camerarius</i> or chamberer was in charge. The surname also applied to clerks employed there. As the office of <i>Chamberlain</i> rose in the social scale, this term remained reserved for more humble servants of the bedchamber or private quarters.","(of Norman origin): habitational name from Les Chambres, Manche (France)."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":21,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Sir William Chamberlain Knight was born about 1238, in Wickenby, Lincolnshire, England as the son of Robert Chamberlayne. He married Mrs Joan Chamberlain about 1261, in North Reston, Lincolnshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died before 1285, in Petsoe Manor, Buckinghamshire, England."},"et":{"about 1238–before 1285":"umbes 1238–enne 1285","1230–1284":"1230–1284","1230–Male":"1230–Surnud","1238–1285":"1238–1285","1251–1313":"1251–1313","1264–1314":"1264–1314","1200–1260":"1200–1260","about 1261":"umbes 1261","1264":"1264","1285":"1285","1230":"1230","1251":"1251","1284":"1284","1260":"1260","1238":"1238","1259":"1259","1314":"1314","1313":"1313","1200":"1200","about 1238":"umbes 1238","before 1285":"enne 1285","North Reston, Lincolnshire, England":"North Reston, Lincolnshire, England","Wickenby, Lincolnshire, England":"Wic